description:
Part of 98b. Second tranche, depends on (a).

## discover-agents.sh
- When no AGENT-REVIEWERS.md is found anywhere in the repo's changed-file tree, call `detect-language.sh`
- Add a `language_detection` block to the JSON output alongside `configuration` and `agents`:
  ```
  {
    "language_detection": {
      "matched": [
        {"language": "golang", "subtree": "backend", "template": "golang.md"},
        {"language": "python", "subtree": "frontend", "template": "python.md"}
      ],
      "same_directory_polyglot": false
    }
  }
  ```
- Detection only fires when AGENT-REVIEWERS.md is ABSENT — repos with existing config are not prompted

## Spawning summary line
- When language detection ran and matched, add a line to the pre-loop spawning summary:
  - `Detected templates: golang (in backend/), python (in frontend/). Run install offer? [see SKILL.md]`
- When all installs are accepted, the next round's spawning summary surfaces the new agents normally
